At 03:05 PM 1/20/2004, Jason Thorpe wrote:
>Only if you wire up the relay incorrectly.  I believe the stock wiring
>configuration is to use alternator output as the signal input to the
>relay, which means the relay would only close if the engine is running.

One more point about isolators vs. relays.  Isolators cause a voltage drop, 
which will hurt charging.  Relays do not.

